Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}. Cut @zucchini{1} into ½-inch cubes. Trim woody bottoms from @asparagus{6%ounce}, then cut into 1-inch pieces. Zest @lemon{1} until you have ½ tsp zest, then cut into halves. Mince half the @chives{¼%ounce}(minced). Pick half the @mint{¼%ounce}(finely chopped) leaves from stems and finely chop.

> TIP: Use the remaining herbs as a garnish, if desired.

== Mint Chive Dressing ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine minced chives, chopped mint, a squeeze of lemon, a
large drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Adjust
to taste with more lemon, salt, and pepper.

== Veggie Succotash ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add onion and
cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Toss in zucchini and cook until lightly
browned and softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove pan
from heat.

== Steak ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in another large pan over medium-high heat. Pat
@sirloin steak{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then season all over with
salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per
side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

Add @peas{4%ounce} and asparagus to pan with succotash. Return pan to stove
over medium-high heat. Cook, tossing, until asparagus is tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat and stir in a squeeze of
lemon and a pinch of lemon zest.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Divide succotash between plates and top
with steak. Drizzle with herb dressing. Garnish with remaining mint leaves and
chives, if desired.